features: Core Boost - With premium layout and fully digital power design to support more cores and provide better performance. Supports 12th Gen Intel Core Processors, Pentium Gold and Celeron Processors for LGA 1700 socket.

High-Speed Connectivity: With PCIe 4.0 technology and multiple M.2 slots, the motherboard provides lightning-fast data transfer speeds, allowing you to connect and use multiple high-speed storage devices with ease.

Enhanced Networking: The motherboard features Wi-Fi 6E technology, providing improved network connectivity with faster speeds and increased capacity. It also supports CFX technology, allowing for multiple graphics cards to be used for enhanced gaming performance.
2.5G LAN and Intel Wi-Fi 6E Solution: Upgraded network solution for professional and multimedia use. Delivers a secure, stable and fast network connection.
M.2 Shield FROZR -Strengthened built-in M.2 thermal solution. Keeps M.2 SSDs safe while preventing throttling, making them run faster.
body.description: PRO series helps users work smarter by delivering an efficient and productive experience. Featuring stable functionality and high-quality assembly, PRO series motherboards provide not only optimized professional workflows but also less troubleshooting and longevity. This has advanced technology to deliver pure data signals for the best performance, stability and compatibility. MSI extended PWM heatsink and enhanced circuit design ensures even high-end processors to run in full speed. Featuring premium 2.5G LAN with LAN manager to deliver better network experience. Detect CPU & GPU temperatures and automatically adjust system fan duty to a proper value. The latest PCIe 5.0 solution with up to 128GB/s bandwidth for maximum transfer speed. Built-in USB 3.2 Gen 2x2 port, offers 20Gbps transmission speed, 4X faster than USB 3.2 Gen 1. Support 4K@60Hz as specified in HDMI 2.1, DisplayPort 1.4 – Requires Processor Graphics.EZ Debug LED Easiest way to troubleshoot Intel Wi-Fi 6 module, Bluetooth 5.2

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Fantastic Motherboard
reviews.reviewText: I've always liked ABIT boards and when they went out of business I switched to MSI and have been a loyal consumer for 20 years or so. MSI motherboards are fast, they always have been.I'm running this board with an I5-12500K, 32GB RAM and an old Evga Hybrid Water cooled 1080 video card. I'm here to tell ya, she flies like the wind, the board and CPU work really well together.A really good machine needs a stable foundation just like a house. That foundation should have a chipset that starts with the letter ZFor better or worse, I would recommend this board model and its manufacturer.
